SENATE BILL 895
E4, F1 6lr3007
CF HB 1328
By: Senator Gile
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Budget and Taxation and Judicial Proceedings
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Safety – Department of State Police – School Mapping Data Program
3 FOR the purpose of repealing certain provisions of law relating to the School Mapping Data
4 Program and providing that the School Safety Subcabinet may provide funding from
5 the Safe Schools Fund to a public safety agency; establishing the School Mapping
6 Data Program in the Department of State Police to provide oversight of and technical
7 assistance to a public safety agency for the production of certain school mapping data
8 for a certain purpose; establishing certain requirements for school mapping data
9 produced by a public safety agency; and generally relating to school mapping data.
10 BY repealing
11 Article – Education
12 Section 5–310.1 and 7–1510.1
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
16 Article – Education
17 Section 7–1512(a), (b), (c), and (f)
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
21 Article – Education
22 Section 7–1512(h)
23 Annotated Code of Maryland
